Kuwait PIC to Shut Fertilizer Plants for Maintenance, Anba Says

-- B y   F i o n a   M a c D o n a l d
-- 
2011-02-13T06:50:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-13/kuwait-pic-to-shut-fertilizer-plants-for-maintenance-anba-says.html
Kuwait’s Petrochemical Industries
Co. plans to close its fertilizer plants in December for one
month for maintenance,  Al-Anba  reported today, citing the
company’s Chairwoman Maha Mulla Hussain.  The shutdown takes place every two years to improve output,
Hussain said, according to the newspaper. The plants produce
about 1 million tons a year of fertilizers, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Fiona MacDonald in Kuwait at 
 fmacdonald4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Shaji Mathew in Dubai at 
 shajimathew@bloomberg.net  